responded: Found it! The `php_libxml_node_free_list` function doesn't have special handling for `XML_DOCUMENT_NODE` or `XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE`. It goes to the default case (lines 205-207) and eventually calls `php_libxml_node_free(node)` at line 215.

So the issue is that when we have a list of nodes that includes document nodes, `php_libxml_node_free_list` will try to free them using `php_libxml_node_free`, which calls `xmlFreeNode` on document nodes. But document nodes should be freed using `xmlFreeDoc`, not `xmlFreeNode`.

The fix should be to add special handling for document nodes in `php_libxml_node_free_list` to skip freeing them, similar to how `php_libxml_node_free_resource` handles them.

